<title>SOUTH AFRICA: African Life lifts year earnings.</title>
<headline>African Life lifts year earnings.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Yr ended March 31, 1997</p>
<p>		(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (cts)		 52.5     vs 32.5</p>
<p>    Div, final (cts)	21.0     vs 16.8</p>
<p>    Total income	    532.6    vs 527.5</p>
<p>    Single premium income 117.2    vs 219.3</p>
<p>    Recurring prem income 415.4    vs 308.2</p>
<p>    Investment income     89.9     vs 64.4</p>
<p>    Attrib surplus	  51.2     vs 32.5</p>
<p>Div on register May 23</p>
<p>Full name: African Life Assurance Co Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said it was well-positioned for the future and expected to maintain real earnings growth.</p>
<p>Shareholders will be offered capitalisation shares in lieu of the cash dividend on the ratio that 21 cents multiplied by 1.05 bears to the weighted average traded share price in the three days to June 19.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
